content:
Creating a Custom Report

You can customize standard reports or build custom reports from scratch to suit your organization's needs.

Available in:
Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience
Essentials, Group, Professional, Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions
Enhanced Folder Sharing and Legacy Folder Sharing

USER PERMISSIONS NEEDED
To run reports: Run Reports (Legacy Folder Sharing, Enhanced Folder Sharing)
To schedule reports: Schedule Reports (Legacy Folder Sharing, Enhanced Folder Sharing)
To create, edit, and delete reports: Create and Customize Reports (Report Builder, Enhanced Folder Sharing)

Manage Custom Report Types permission defines custom report types that extend the types of reports from which all users can create or update custom reports. A report type defines records and fields available to a report based on relationships between primary object and related objects.

Manage Reporting Snapshots permission creates and schedules snapshots. Reporting snapshot lets you report on historical data. Authorized users can save tabular or summary report results to fields on a custom object, then map those fields to corresponding fields on a target object. They can schedule when to run the report to load the custom object's fields with the report's data.

Users with Manage Custom Report Types and Manage Reporting Snapshots permissions can define custom report types and create reporting snapshots respectively.
title: Customizing Reports in Salesforce
